==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ad valorem
<hw>Ad va*lo"rem</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[L., according to the
value.]</ety> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>A term used to denote a duty or
charge laid upon goods, at a certain rate per cent upon their value, as
stated in their invoice, -- in opposition to a specific sum upon a given
quantity or number; <as>as, an <ex>ad valorem</ex> duty of twenty per
cent</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Advance</ent>⟦br⟧
